  "section_name": "Risk Analysis",
  "text": "American Express carries moderate financial leverage risk as of Q3 2025. Total debt stands at $57,787,000,000 against stockholders' equity of $32,417,000,000, resulting in a debt-to-equity ratio of 1.78. However, the company maintains substantial liquidity with cash and equivalents of $54,706,000,000, yielding a net debt position of only $3,081,000,000. This suggests the company has adequate cash resources to service its debt obligations, though the leverage ratio indicates reliance on borrowed capital to fund operations and growth initiatives.",
